<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan=2><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> September 30, 2001</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>BACK AMONGST US</p><font class='news'>As a follow up to our story regarding mass account bannings last week (see September 28 news), according to latest information it appears that most players are having their accounts <u>re-instated</u>.<P>
No statement from Sony has yet been issued regarding the bannings or the re-instatements.<P>
Once again a reminder that is against the EULA to use any third party programs on EverQuest files.  If you are unsure on whether a program violates the EULA or not you can send an email to <a href="mailto:eqaccountstatus@station.sony.com">eqaccountstatus@station.sony.com</a>.

</font>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Baelish</a></font>, 6:37 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr>
  	<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan=2><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> September 29, 2001</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>ALIGNMENT INFO SHEET</p><font class='news'>With the release of the new Alignments Role Playing Server an entire new aspect has been added to EverQuest: Alignments. To better understand how alignment will influence your next character Verant has compiled all the information regarding race, class, diety, and overall alignment together.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3812'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 2:02 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>FEMALE LUCLIN PICS</p><font class='news'>We have received some screenshots of the new barbarian female model to be released as part of the new EverQuest engine with the Shadows of Luclin expansion slated for December.<P>
Click <a href="/screenshots2/default.asp?category=4">here</a> to see our Luclin screenshot collection.
<P>Update: These are barbarian, not human as first reported.</p
</font>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Baelish</a></font>, 1:42 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>ALIGNMENT SERVER UP</p><font class='news'>The Alignment/Role Playing Server "Firiona Vie" is now open for testing! You can access this new server by running the test server patch program, testeverquest.exe. Remember that this server is in <i>beta</i> and your characters will <i>not</i> be saved when it goes live!
</font>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 1:22 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr>
  	<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan=2><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> September 28, 2001</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>MORE RP SERVER NEWS</p><font class='news'>More news on the upcoming Role Playing server has been released. Brad McQuaid stopped by the Developer's Corner message board today to post these new tidbits. First of all, the server will show up on the selection screen as "Firiona Vie (Role-playing preferred)" and secondly, he clarified that the /emote command will use the language of the speaker but not canned emotes such as /wave.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3809'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 2:57 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>MASS ACCOUNT BANNINGS</p><font class='news'><p>There has recently been a large number of bannings of player accounts as a
result of allegedly using third party software to alter the EQ-Client. 
Sony have not yet made any official statement regarding this latest crackdown,
but players across a number of servers have been supposedly caught for violating
the EULA</p>
<p>Whilst we will continue to follow up on this with Sony you can read the
account of some players affected from Tribunal <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showMessage?topicID=654.topic" target="_blank">here</a>. 
Many players feel that they have been unjustly accused of the claim, and Sony
has, according to players, failed to provide any proof or evidence via logs or otherwise..</p>
<p>The EULA states the following:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>9. You may not use any third party software to modify the Software to change Game play. You may not use our intellectual property rights contained in the Game or the Software to create or provide any other means through which the Game may be played by others, as through server emulators. You may not take any action which imposes an unreasonable or disproportionately large load on our infrastructure. You may not sell or auction any EverQuest characters, items, coin or copyrighted material.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you want to be 100% sure that you will not have your account banned for
third party program reasons do not ever use any software of any kind to alter
any EQ files other than the EverQuest patcher.</p>
<p>We will post updates if Sony release any  information as to why such a
large number of accounts have recently been banned.</p>
<P>You can discuss this incident in our Burning Issues forum by clicking <a href="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic&f=3&t=002696">here</a>.</font>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Baelish</a></font>, 2:55 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>ASK BRAD!</p><font class='news'>Brad McQuaid returns to the Developer's Corner today with another installment of his general QA post "Ask Brad!" Many topics are covered as usual, ranging from Luclin graphics to what Brad prefers with his fries.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3807'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 2:54 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr>
  	<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan=2><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> September 27, 2001</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>PATCH MESSAGE</p><font class='news'>Today's patch message is out with the only fix being a correction to the ASCII text bug which went in with the September 25 patch.</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3806'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Baelish</a></font>, 3:58 PM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>TEXT BUG</p><font class='news'>Since the last patch a new text bug has been introduced that causes several emotes to be displayed incorrectly. Absor announced that Verant is aware of this bug and it will be fixed soon.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3805'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 3:53 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>ALIGNMENT SERVER QA</p><font class='news'>Alan took a moment to answer a few new questions that have cropped up regarding the alignment server. First Alan discussed how alignment will relate to NPCs and second how the trivial loot code will effect many quests.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3804'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 3:50 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>EMERGENCY PATCH</p><font class='news'>An emergency patch has been announced to fix some bugs that were recently introduced:
<p><blockquote><i>On Thursday, September 27th, at 3AM PDT (10AM GMT), all servers will be coming down for an emergency patch. The estimated downtime is 3 hours. 

<p>- The EverQuest Operations Team</blockquote></i>
</font>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 1:09 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr>
  	<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan=2><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> September 26, 2001</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>CHOOSE YOUR ALIGNMENT!</p><font class='news'>The long awaited rules for the Role Playing server, now known as the Alignment server have been released! Included are some old ideas, such as server wide trivial loot code and no no-drop items, but also some new ones such as experience bonuses and penalties revolving around your parties alignment.
</font><p class='db'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3802'><b>here</b></a> for details.</p>    <p class='newsig'><font class='newsig'>Submitted by </font><font class='newsiglink'><a href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com' class='newsiglink'>Kivlan</a></font>, 2:27 AM</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>  </tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>DON'T CELEBRATE YET</p><font class='news'>While some rangers may have noticed that their double attack skill was upgraded from 235 to 245 in the last patch don't start thanking Verant yet. According to Absor this change was <u>unintentional</u> and it is unknown whether it will remain on live servers.
