<tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr>  <tr>    <td valign='top' align='left' class='news'><p class='boldheader'>RUMOR MILL</p><font class='news'>According to current rumors floating around the upcoming PC Gamer magazine has some interesting facts regarding Shadows of Luclin, in partiuclar horses:
<ul>
<li>Paladins may be able to summon lower end horses by use of a spell.</li>
<li>Horses will range in cost from 9,000pp to 15,000pp.</li>
<li>The Vah Shir classes are confirmed to be Bards, Rogues, Warriors, Shamans, and Beastlords.  They also get safe fall as a racial ability, and consume food faster than other races. </li>
<li>If fighting unarmed, it's supposed the Beastlord will gain an armor bonus due to their affinity to the animals. At higher levels, skills such as Brawling Bear, Frenzied Tiger, Swooping Eagle, and Striking Snake all highlight the strong animal kinship.</li>
<li>A new particle effect engine is also in testing phases.</li>
</ul>
Right now these are rumors as we haven't been able to land a copy of the magazine, but it seems these are a pretty accurate reflection of the article so far.
